Package johar.interfaceinterpreter.star

Interface Summary
CommandControllerBase This interface interacts with the Widgets; It performs any action required by the user, while handling all events generated by the Widgets; It interacts with the Gem via GemSetting and the Idf to serve requests raised from the Widgets.
 

Class Summary
AddMoreButton Used for creating the Add Another button in a parameter widget (in the Command Dialog).
BooleanWidget This is the widget for every boolean parameter.
BrowsableTableModel Model for Browsable Tables.
ChoiceWidget This is the widget for every choice parameter.
CommandCancelButton Used for creating the Cancel button in the Command Dialog.
CommandController The Command Controller class interacts with the Widgets; It performs any action required by the user, while handling all events generated by the Widgets; It interacts with the Gem via GemSetting and the Idf to serve requests raised from the Widgets.
CommandDialog The Command Dialog Box creator.
CommandMenu A Menu in the Star GUI.
CommandMenuItem A Menu Item in the Star GUI.
CommandOKButton Used for creating the OK button in the Command Dialog.
DateWidget This is the widget for every date parameter.
DeleteButton Used for creating the Delete button for a repetition in a parameter widget (in the Command Dialog).
FileWidget This is the widget for every file parameter.
HelpBackButton The Back button on the Help Dialog Box.
HelpContents Creates the contents of the Help Dialog Box.
HelpDialog This class creates a Help Box with three states: the Top-Level state, the Command state, and the Parameter/Question state.
HelpOKButton The OK button on the Help Dialog Box.
HelpTableModel Model for Help Tables.
IdfAnalyzer Provides access to various information about the specified IDF (e.g list of queryable/non-queryable params in a command/stage, list of questions in a command, list of tables, list of browsable tables, etc.).
MessageDialog Message Dialog Box for showing messages to users.
MoveDownButton Used for creating the Move Down button for a repetition in a parameter widget (in the Command Dialog).
MoveUpButton Used for creating the Move Up button for a repetition in a parameter widget (in the Command Dialog).
NextButton Used for creating the Next button in the Command Dialog.
NonBrowsableTableModel Model for Non-Browsable Tables.
NumberFilter Makes a text field to accept only numeric values - integers and float-point numbers.
NumberWidget This is the widget for every int or float parameter.
ParameterWidget This class creates widget for each queryable parameter.
PreviousButton Used for creating the Previous button in the Command Dialog.
QuestionCancelButton The OK button on the Question Dialog Box.
QuestionDialog The Question Dialog Box for each question attribute in the IDF.
QuestionOKButton The OK button on the Question Dialog Box.
ScrollingWidget Attaches scrollbars to widgets.
StageGUI Creates parameter widgets for each queryable stage.
Star The Star Interface Interpreter main class.
StarWindow The Main Window or Frame of the Star Interface Interpreter.
StatusBar The Status Bar in the Star Window.
TableArea The Table Area in the Star Window.
TableCellRenderer Cell Renderer for all Help tables.
TableEntryWidget This is the widget for every table entry parameter with a non-browsable SourceTable.
TableWidget Table Widget in the Table Area or Help Dialog Box.
TextDisplayArea Text Display Area of the Star Window.
TextFilter A filter for a text field which constrains the user to enter text that does not exceed the specified maximum number of characters.
TextWidget This is the widget for every text parameter.
TimeWidget This is the widget for every timeOfDay parameter.
WidgetAnalyzer Searches for widgets in containers; It also retrieves values in widgets.
